    <item>
      <title>Part I. Philosophical Teachings of Bitcoin</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-1/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 21 Dec 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-1/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;book-expand&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;label&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;book-expand-head flex justify-between&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span&gt;Contents&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span&gt;...&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;checkbox&#34; class=&#34;hidden&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;book-expand-content markdown-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-1&#34;&gt;Part I. Philosophical Teachings of Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-2&#34;&gt;Part II. Economic Teachings of Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-3&#34;&gt;Part III. Technological Teachings of Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;book-hint btc&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;This article by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/dergigi&#34;&gt;Gigi&lt;/a&gt; was published on &lt;a href=&#34;https://dergigi.com/2018/12/21/philosophical-teachings-of-bitcoin&#34;&gt;dergigi.com&lt;/a&gt; website.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/contribute/&#34;&gt;Contribute&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Some questions have easy answers. “What have you learned from Bitcoin?” isn’t one of them. After trying to answer this question in a short tweet, and failing miserably, I realized that the amount of things I’ve learned is far too numerous to answer quickly, if at all. I also realized that any set of answers to this question will be different for everyone — a reflection of the very personal journey through the wonderful world of crypto. Hence, the subtitle of this series is &lt;em&gt;What I’ve Learned From Bitcoin&lt;/em&gt;, with which I want to acknowledge the inherent personal bias of answering a question like this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Part II. Economic Teachings of Bitcoin</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-2/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 11 Jan 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;book-expand&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;label&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;book-expand-head flex justify-between&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span&gt;Contents&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span&gt;...&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;checkbox&#34; class=&#34;hidden&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;book-expand-content markdown-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-1&#34;&gt;Part I. Philosophical Teachings of Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-2&#34;&gt;Part II. Economic Teachings of Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-3&#34;&gt;Part III. Technological Teachings of Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;book-hint btc&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;This article by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/dergigi&#34;&gt;Gigi&lt;/a&gt; was published on &lt;a href=&#34;https://dergigi.com/2019/01/11/economic-teachings-of-bitcoin&#34;&gt;dergigi.com&lt;/a&gt; website.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/contribute/&#34;&gt;Contribute&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Money doesn’t grow on trees. To believe that it does is foolish, and our parents make sure that we know about that by repeating this saying like a mantra. We are encouraged to use money wisely, to not spend it frivolously, and to save it in good times to help us through the bad. Money, after all, does not grow on trees.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Part III. Technological Teachings of Bitcoin</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-3/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 02 Apr 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-3/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;book-expand&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;label&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;book-expand-head flex justify-between&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span&gt;Contents&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span&gt;...&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;input type=&#34;checkbox&#34; class=&#34;hidden&#34; /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;book-expand-content markdown-inner&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-1&#34;&gt;Part I. Philosophical Teachings of Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-2&#34;&gt;Part II. Economic Teachings of Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/en/what-i-learned-from-bitcoin-3&#34;&gt;Part III. Technological Teachings of Bitcoin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/label&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;book-hint btc&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;This article by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/dergigi&#34;&gt;Gigi&lt;/a&gt; was published on &lt;a href=&#34;https://dergigi.com/2019/04/02/technological-teachings-of-bitcoin/&#34;&gt;dergigi.com&lt;/a&gt; website.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/contribute/&#34;&gt;Contribute&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;What is Bitcoin? The many answers to this question are as interesting as they are varied. Bitcoin is both a social and a monetary phenomenon, but it is also a technological one. The intersection of many disciplines is what makes Bitcoin endlessly fascinating. Like many others, I began to stumble down this strange rabbit hole a while ago. Even though this article is the last of this series, I am still stumbling down with no end in sight, and I invite you to stumble along with me.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
